# Responsive — Mobile & Web

**Mobile-first always.** Style base for phone, enhance with `sm:` `md:` `lg:` breakpoints.

| Breakpoint | Width | Use |
|------------|-------|-----|
| (default) | < 640px | Phone — single column, stacked UI |
| `sm:` | ≥ 640px | Large phone / small tablet |
| `md:` | ≥ 768px | Tablet — 2-column grids |
| `lg:` | ≥ 1024px | Desktop — full nav, sidebars |

## Layout

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — mobile stack → desktop grid
<div className="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">

// ✅ GOOD — container padding scales
<div className="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

// ❌ BAD — desktop-only fixed width
<div className="w-[1200px]">
```

Use project utilities from `index.css`: `.container-page`, `.section-padding`, `.section-title`.

## Navigation

- Desktop (`lg:`): horizontal nav in `Header`.
- Mobile: `Sheet` / hamburger menu — never hide critical links without a mobile alternative.
- Admin: collapsible sidebar or sheet on `< lg`.

```tsx
<nav className="hidden lg:flex">...</nav>
<Sheet>...</Sheet>  {/* lg:hidden trigger */}
```

## Tables & lists (admin)

Dual view on small screens:

| Viewport | Pattern |
|----------|---------|
| `< md` | Card list — label + value per row |
| `≥ md` | Data table |

Never horizontal-scroll-only tables without a card fallback on mobile.

## Forms

```tsx
<div className="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">  {/* stack on phone */}
<Button className="w-full sm:w-auto">       {/* full-width CTA on mobile */}
```

## Touch & readability

- Tap targets: **min 44×44px** (`min-h-11 min-w-11` or `size-11` for icon buttons).
- Body text: `text-base` on mobile; `md:text-lg` for lead paragraphs only.
- Avoid hover-only actions — expose same action via tap/visible button on mobile.

## Images & media

```tsx
<img className="h-auto w-full object-cover" />
// Hero: shorter on mobile
<div className="min-h-[50vh] md:min-h-[70vh]">
```

## Testing checklist

- [ ] 375px (iPhone SE) — no overflow-x, readable text
- [ ] 768px (tablet) — grid transitions cleanly
- [ ] 1280px (desktop) — full layout, no excessive whitespace

